Russian billionaire Andrey Melnichenko ordered construction of the worldâ€™s largest sailing
yacht for about $100 million,  CNBC  reported today, citing
unidentified people in the shipbuilding industry.  The boat, about 400-feet (122-meters) long, will be built
at the Nobiskrug shipyard in  Germany  and completed by 2015 or
2016, CNBC said.  Melnichenko, the main owner of coal producer SUEK and
fertilizer maker EuroChem, is worth $11.7 billion, according to
